ETYMOLOGY: From Old English nigen, from Proto-Germanic *niwun, from Proto-Indo-European *h₁newn̥.

MEANINGS.DEF_EN: The cardinal number equivalent to the sum of one and eight; one more than eight.
MEANINGS.DEF_ZH: 八加一的和；介于八和十之间的自然数。
MEANINGS.SENT_EN: There are nine planets in the solar system, depending on how you count them.
MEANINGS.SENT_ZH: 根据你如何计算，太阳系有九颗行星。

MEANINGS.POS_TIP: A word (other than a pronoun) used to identify any of a class of people, places, or things (common noun), or to name a particular one of these (proper noun).
MEANINGS.DEF_EN: A group or set of nine things or people.
MEANINGS.DEF_ZH: 由九个事物或人组成的集体。
MEANINGS.SENT_EN: The committee consists of a nine of expert advisors.
MEANINGS.SENT_ZH: 该委员会由九名专家顾问组成。

MEANINGS.POS_TIP: A group of words established by usage as having a meaning not deducible from those of the individual words.
MEANINGS.DEF_EN: To the highest degree of perfection or style; perfectly.
MEANINGS.DEF_ZH: 达到最高程度的完美或时尚；完美地。
MEANINGS.SENT_EN: She was dressed to the nines for the gala event.
MEANINGS.SENT_ZH: 她为了盛大的晚会打扮得光彩照人。
